text: Alternatively, Singapore could be called 'multicultural' and whatever it is the western world in general is doing is something entirely different and clearly vastly worse.
... Also, Nowrasteh takes the "Idiot or malignant liar?" question to zones of extremity previously thought unimaginable.
Heard about the children's classic 'My Two Mummies Wear the Hijab' yesterday, but no one told me Stancil had written it.

It's complicated. 
For sound, exoteric liberalism, though, minding your own business is the best way to harmonize with The Invisible Hands.
